  "body": "# Bug Report\r\nStatus.AppImage fails to run on Linux due to a readonly filesystem issue\r\n\r\n## Description\r\nstatus-desktop tries to create dataDir/tmpDir/logDir in readonly AppImage filesystem\r\n```\r\n$ ./Status.AppImage \r\ndataDir /tmp/.mount_StatusKOw5EG/usr/Status/\r\ntmpDir /tmp/.mount_StatusKOw5EG/usr/Status/tmp/\r\nlogDir /tmp/.mount_StatusKOw5EG/usr/Status/logs/\r\n/home/o/Dev/status/status-desktop/src/nim_status_client.nim(168) nim_status_client\r\n/home/o/Dev/status/status-desktop/src/nim_status_client.nim(80) mainProc\r\n/home/o/Dev/status/status-desktop/src/constants.nim(67) ensureDirectories\r\n/home/o/Dev/status/status-desktop/vendor/nimbus-build-system/vendor/Nim/lib/pure/os.nim(2312) createDir\r\n/home/o/Dev/status/status-desktop/vendor/nimbus-build-system/vendor/Nim/lib/pure/os.nim(2282) existsOrCreateDir\r\n/home/o/Dev/status/status-desktop/vendor/nimbus-build-system/vendor/Nim/lib/pure/os.nim(2254) rawCreateDir\r\n/home/o/Dev/status/status-desktop/vendor/nimbus-build-system/vendor/Nim/lib/pure/includes/oserr.nim(94) raiseOSError\r\nError: unhandled exception: Read-only file system\r\nAdditional info: \"/tmp/.mount_StatusKOw5EG/usr/Status\" [OSError]\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- Provide a short description describing the problem you are experiencing. -->\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1) checkout dogfooding/phase4\r\n2) make pkg\r\n3) cd pkg && chmod a+x Status.AppImage\r\n4) ./Status.AppImage\r\n\r\n<!-- example: step 1. do X step 2. do Y etc.. -->\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: dogfooding/phase4\r\n\r\n- Operating System: Ubuntu 21.10",
